Issues.Body:
Using **ng serve** the compiler will detect any changes and auto-recompile/build.
During development making minor changes sometimes causes an error. The compiler correctly shows the error, I remove the offending code, then it recompiles but still shows the  error!

If I stop and restart  '**ng serve**' then it recompiles with no errors!

**Angular CLI**: 11.0.2
**Node**: 14.4.0

**Package**                                  **Version**
---------------------------------------------------------
@angular-devkit/architect           0.1100.2
@angular-devkit/build-angular   0.1100.2
@angular-devkit/core                   11.0.2
@angular-devkit/schematics       11.0.2
@angular/cdk                                11.0.1
@angular/material                         11.0.1
@schematics/angular                   11.0.2
@schematics/update                    0.1100.2

**OS:** MacOs Big Sur V11.01

Only happened since the upgrade to **Angular 11**
Happens on all browsers

This appears to be a similar issue to  [https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/issues/5404] (issue 5404 closed)

